{{see|vega}}

==English==
===Etymology 1===
From Medieval Latin < {{Arab.}} {{ARchar|[[واقع]]}} (''wāqi‘'', [[fall]]ing), from the expression
{{ARchar|[[نسر|النسر]] [[واقع|الواقع]]}} ''(an-nasr al-wāqi‘'', [[fall]]ing [[eagle]]). The active participle {{ARchar|[[واقع]]}} derives from the verb {{ARchar|[[وقع]]}} (''wáqa‘a'', to fall, drop, tumble, alight, pounce).

====Proper noun====
{{wikipedia}}
'''Vega'''

#{{star}}: The brightest [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Lyra]]; Alpha (α) Lyrae. It forms one corner of the [[Summer Triangle]].

